tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows significantly elevated creatinine, marked proteinuria, glucosuria, and ketonuria, with low urine specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance, suggesting impaired renal function, likely chronic kidney disease with possible nephrotic features and glycosuria not explained by low-normal blood glucose and low HbA1c. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Further nephrological evaluation and assessment for possible underlying diabetes or other metabolic disorders are recommended.
